predicates.description: If PV1-20.1 (Financial Class.Financial Class Code) is valued 'T' (third party).

conformanceStatements.description: If PV1-20.1 (Financial Class.Financial Class Code) is 'T' (Third Party) or 'P' (Patient) then PID-11 (Patient Address) SHALL include an address with type 'H'.
conformanceStatements.assertion:
<Assertion xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
						<IMPLY>
							<!-- make sure to check for presence -->
							<AND>
								<Presence Path="5[1].1[1].20[1].1[1]"/>
								<StringList CSV="T,P" Path="5[1].1[1].20[1].1[1]"/>
							</AND>
							<!-- PID-11 can repeat -->
							<!-- [TODO] check if this is working. check with a PID-11.7 present, but NOT valued 'H' -->
							<AND>
								<Presence Path="1[1].11[*].7[1]"/>
								<PlainText IgnoreCase="false" Path="1[1].11[*].7[1]" Text="H"/>
							</AND>
						</IMPLY>
					</Assertion>

conformanceStatements.description: If PV1-20.1 (Financial Class.Financial Class Code) is valued 'T' (Third Party) or 'P' (Patient), PID-5.7 (Name Type Code) SHALL be valued 'L'.
conformanceStatements.assertion:
<Assertion xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
						<IMPLY>
							<!-- make sure to check for presence -->
							<AND>
								<Presence Path="5[1].1[1].20[1].1[1]"/>
								<StringList CSV="T,P" Path="5[1].1[1].20[1].1[1]"/>
							</AND>
							<!-- PID.5 does not repeat -->
							<AND>
								<Presence Path="1[1].5[1].7[1]"/>
								<PlainText IgnoreCase="false" Path="1[1].5[1].7[1]" Text="L"/>
							</AND>
						</IMPLY>
					</Assertion>

conformanceStatements.description: The value of OBX-1 (Set ID - OBX) SHALL be valued sequentially starting the value '1' within a given segment group.
The value of SPM-1 (Set ID - SPM) SHALL start at '1' and be incremented sequentially within the Order Group.

predicates.description: If OBR-28 (Result Copies To) is valued.
If OBR-7 (Observation Date/Time) in the same Observation Request group is valued.

conformanceStatements.description: For each value in OBR-28 (Result Copies To) a corresponding PRT (Participant Information) SHALL be present with PRT-4.1 (Participation Identifier) valued 'RCT'.
For each PRT (Participant Information) where PRT-4.1 (Participation.Identifier) is valued 'RCT' there must be a corresponding value in OBR-28 (Result Copies To) equal to PRT-5 (Participation Person).

If there are multiple OBX segments associated with the same OBR or SPM segment that have the same OBX-3 (Observation Identifier) values for (OBX-3.1 (Identifier) and OBX-3.3 (Name of Coding System) or (OBX-3.4 (Alternate Identifier) and OBX-3.6 (Name of Alternate Coding System)), a combination of (OBX-3.1 and OBX3.3) or (OBX-3.4 and OBX-3.6) and OBX-4 (Observation Sub-ID) SHALL create a unique identification under a single OBR.
Only one instance of DG1-15 (Diagnosis Priority) in the message SHALL contain the value '1'.

If any of OBR-7 (Observation Date/Time), OBR-8 (Observation End Date/Time), SPM-17.1 (Range Start Date/Time) or SPM-17.2 (Range End Date/Time) contain a time zone offset then all SHALL contain a time zone offset.
conformanceStatements.assertion:
<Assertion xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
						<OR>
							<FORALL>
								<!-- OBR-7 is not present OR it contains TZ offset -->
								<OR>
									<NOT>
										<Presence Path="1[1].7[1].1[1]"/>
									</NOT>
									<Format Path="1[1].7[1].1[1]" Regex=".*(-|\+).*"/>
								</OR>
								<!-- OBR-8 is not present OR it contains TZ offset -->
								<OR>
									<NOT>
										<Presence Path="1[1].8[1].1[1]"/>
									</NOT>
									<Format Path="1[1].8[1].1[1]" Regex=".*(-|\+).*"/>
								</OR>
								<!-- SPM-17.1 is not present OR it contains TZ offset -->
								<OR>
									<NOT>
										<Presence Path="8[1].17[1].1[1].1[1]"/>
									</NOT>
									<Format Path="8[1].17[1].1[1].1[1]" Regex=".*(-|\+).*"/>
								</OR>
								<!-- SPM-17.2 is not present OR it contains TZ offset -->
								<OR>
									<NOT>
										<Presence Path="8[1].17[1].2[1].1[1]"/>
									</NOT>
									<Format Path="8[1].17[1].2[1].1[1]" Regex=".*(-|\+).*"/>
								</OR>
							</FORALL>
							<FORALL>
								<!-- OBR-7 is not present OR it does not contains TZ offset -->
								<OR>
									<NOT>
										<Presence Path="1[1].7[1].1[1]"/>
									</NOT>
									<Format Path="1[1].7[1].1[1]" Regex="[^-+]*"/>
								</OR>
								<!-- OBR-8 is not present OR it does not contains TZ offset -->
								<OR>
									<NOT>
										<Presence Path="1[1].8[1].1[1]"/>
									</NOT>
									<Format Path="1[1].8[1].1[1]" Regex="[^-+]*"/>
								</OR>
								<!-- SPM-17.1 is not present OR it does not contains TZ offset -->
								<OR>
									<NOT>
										<Presence Path="8[1].17[1].1[1].1[1]"/>
									</NOT>
									<Format Path="8[1].17[1].1[1].1[1]" Regex="[^-+]*"/>
								</OR>
								<!-- SPM-17.2 is not present OR it does not contains TZ offset -->
								<OR>
									<NOT>
										<Presence Path="8[1].17[1].2[1].1[1]"/>
									</NOT>
									<Format Path="8[1].17[1].2[1].1[1]" Regex="[^-+]*"/>
								</OR>
							</FORALL>
						</OR>
					</Assertion>

conformanceStatements.description: The value of ORC-2 (Placer Order Number) SHALL be identical to the value of OBR-2 (Placer Order Number) within the same Order Group.
conformanceStatements.assertion:
<Assertion xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
						<FORALL>
							<PathValue Operator="EQ" Path1="1[1].2[1].1[1]" Path2="3[1].1[1].2[1].1[1]"/>
							<PathValue Operator="EQ" Path1="1[1].2[1].2[1]" Path2="3[1].1[1].2[1].2[1]"/>
							<PathValue Operator="EQ" Path1="1[1].2[1].3[1]" Path2="3[1].1[1].2[1].3[1]"/>
							<PathValue Operator="EQ" Path1="1[1].2[1].4[1]" Path2="3[1].1[1].2[1].4[1]"/>
						</FORALL>
					</Assertion>

conformanceStatements.description: If valued, ORC-3 (Filler Order Number) SHALL be identical to the value of OBR-3 (Filler Order Number) within the same Order Group.
conformanceStatements.assertion:
<Assertion xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
						<FORALL>
							<PathValue Operator="EQ" Path1="1[1].3[1].1[1]" Path2="3[1].1[1].3[1].1[1]"/>
							<PathValue Operator="EQ" Path1="1[1].3[1].2[1]" Path2="3[1].1[1].3[1].2[1]"/>
							<PathValue Operator="EQ" Path1="1[1].3[1].3[1]" Path2="3[1].1[1].3[1].3[1]"/>
							<PathValue Operator="EQ" Path1="1[1].3[1].4[1]" Path2="3[1].1[1].3[1].4[1]"/>
						</FORALL>
					</Assertion>

conformanceStatements.description: The value of ORC-12 (Ordering Provider) SHALL be identical to the value of OBR-16 (Ordering Provider) within the same Order Group.
The value of OBR-1 (Set ID - OBR) SHALL start at '1' and be incremented sequentially across the Order groups.

An occurrence of MSH-21 (Message Profile Identifier) SHALL be valued with '2.16.840.1.113883.9.87' (LOI_NG_PRU_Profile) or three occurrences SHALL be valued with '2.16.840.1.113883.9.66' (LOI_Common_Component), '2.16.840.1.113883.9.79' (LOI_NG_Component) and '2.16.840.1.113883.9.82' (LAB_PRU_Component) in any order.
The value of ORC-2 (Placer Order Number) SHALL NOT be valued identical to another instance of ORC-2 (Placer Order Number) within the same message excluding the Prior Result group(s).
